<h3
    data-c-font-size="h3"
    data-c-colour="c1"
    data-c-font-weight="600"
    data-c-padding="top(double)"
    data-c-margin="bottom(normal)">
    Installing Your Menu
</h3>

<p data-c-margin="bottom(normal)">Installing your menu of choice requires two main steps, followed by customization as described in the following section.</p>

<p data-c-margin="bottom(normal)">To begin, we need to give the <code class="language-html">{% filter escape %}<body>{% endfilter %}</code> tag a unique <code class="language-html">{% filter escape %}data-c-menu-style{% endfilter %}</code> attribute to determine the menu's type:</p>

<pre><code class="language-html">{% filter escape %}<!--Topbar Menus-->
<body data-clone data-c-menu-style="topbar">

<!--Sidebar Menus-->
<body data-clone data-c-menu-style="sidebar">{% endfilter %}</code></pre>

<p data-c-margin="tb(normal)">Once this is done, you can move forward by installing the menu proper inside your <code class="language-html">{% filter escape %}<body>{% endfilter %}</code> element using the following markup:</p>

<pre><code class="language-html">{% filter escape %}{% include "../../../node_modules/clone-framework/app/twig/components/menu.twig" %}{% endfilter %}</code></pre>

